    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. so it's basically just a way to make sure nobody gets ripped off? what kind of stuff actually goes into the escrow account besides the deposit? like is it just cash or is there more to it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Exactly, it's a giant safety net to prevent anyone from being swindled! In the escrow account, it's not just the initial deposit, though that's a big part of it. You'll typically see other funds going in, like the remaining purchase price minus any down payment already made, and sometimes funds designated for closing costs. These costs can include things like legal fees, title insurance, and property taxes that need to be settled at the time of closing. The escrow agent keeps all these moving parts organized until the final handshake.",
